xternal GPU via the ROG XG Mobile interface.',14),(52,'Can I install PC games from Steam or Epic?','Yes, it\'s a Windows 11 device and supports all PC game platforms.',14),(53,'What is the refresh rate of the screen?','It has a 120Hz full HD 7-inch display with touch support.',14),(54,'Is it good for emulation and cloud gaming?','Yes, it\'s perfect for both — runs emulators smoothly and supports Xbox Cloud Gaming.',14),(55,'Can I install Android apps on this?','Yes, it supports Google Play so you can install compatible Android apps.',15),(56,'Is this meant only for cloud gaming?','It\'s optimized for cloud gaming but can run local Android apps too.',15),(57,'Does it support Xbox remote play?','Yes, you can stream games directly from your Xbox console over Wi-Fi.',15),(58,'How long does the battery last?','You can expect over 12 hours of usage with regular gaming.',15),(59,'Can I connect the Switch Lite to a TV?','No, the Switch Lite is only for handheld gaming and doesn’t support TV output.',16),(60,'Can I play all Switch games on it?','You can play all games that support handheld mode. Some games may require external Joy-Cons.',16),(61,'Does it support multiplayer?','Yes, it supports local wireless and online multiplayer when connected to the internet.',16),(62,'How long does the battery last?','Depending on the game, battery lasts between 3 to 7 hours on a full charge.',16),(63,'Is the OLED Switch compatible with old Switch games?','Yes, it plays all Nintendo Switch physical and digital games.',17),(64,'Can I connect the Switch OLED to a TV?','Yes, it includes a dock with HDMI and a new LAN port for TV play and wired internet.',17),(65,'How long does the battery last?','Depending on the game, it lasts between 4.5 to 9 hours.',17),(66,'Does it come with Joy-Cons?','Yes, detachable Joy-Cons are included and support motion control and HD rumble.',17),(67,'Does the PS5 support PS4 games?','Yes, the PS5 is backward compatible with most PS4 games and accessories.',19),(